# 2. DeviceInfoActivity Design (UI + Data Mapping)

## 🎯 Objective

Build a **clean, dynamic screen** that shows:

* Hardware info
* Software info
* Network info

Focus:

* Fast loading
* Structured display
* Easy to extend

---

# 🧩 Screen Layout Structure

```text
ScrollView
  └── LinearLayout (Vertical)
        ├── Device Summary Card
        ├── Hardware Section
        ├── Software Section
        └── Network Section
```

---

# 📱 1. Device Summary Card (Top Section)

## 🎯 Purpose:

Quick overview (most important info at a glance)

## UI:

```text
[ 📱 Device Name ]
Model: XYZ
Manufacturer: ABC
Android: 14 (API 34)
```

## Data Mapping:

| Field           | Source                |
| --------------- | --------------------- |
| Device Name     | Build.MODEL           |
| Manufacturer    | Build.MANUFACTURER    |
| Android Version | Build.VERSION.RELEASE |
| API Level       | Build.VERSION.SDK_INT |

---

# ⚙️ 2. Hardware Section

## 🎯 Purpose:

Show physical specs

## UI:

```text
⚙️ Hardware

CPU ABI: arm64-v8a
Cores: 8

RAM: 8GB total
Available: 3.2GB

Storage: 128GB total
Free: 60GB
```

---

## 🔧 Data Mapping

### CPU Info

```java
String abi = Build.SUPPORTED_ABIS[0];
```

### CPU Cores

```java
Runtime.getRuntime().availableProcessors();
```

---

### RAM Info

```java
ActivityManager am = (ActivityManager) getSystemService(ACTIVITY_SERVICE);
ActivityManager.MemoryInfo memInfo = new ActivityManager.MemoryInfo();
am.getMemoryInfo(memInfo);

long totalRam = memInfo.totalMem;
long availRam = memInfo.availMem;
```

---

### Storage Info

```java
StatFs stat = new StatFs(Environment.getDataDirectory().getPath());

long blockSize = stat.getBlockSizeLong();
long totalBlocks = stat.getBlockCountLong();
long availableBlocks = stat.getAvailableBlocksLong();

long totalStorage = totalBlocks * blockSize;
long freeStorage = availableBlocks * blockSize;
```

---

# 💻 3. Software Section

## 🎯 Purpose:

System-level details

## UI:

```text
💻 Software

Android Version: 14
API Level: 34
Kernel: 5.x.x
Build ID: ABC123
Security Patch: 2024-03
```

---

## 🔧 Data Mapping

```java
String version = Build.VERSION.RELEASE;
int api = Build.VERSION.SDK_INT;
String buildId = Build.ID;
String securityPatch = Build.VERSION.SECURITY_PATCH;
```

---

### Kernel Version

```java
System.getProperty("os.version");
```

---

# 📡 4. Network Section

## 🎯 Purpose:

Current connectivity state

## UI:

```text
📡 Network

Connection: Wi-Fi
IP Address: 192.168.x.x
Status: Connected
```

---

## 🔧 Data Mapping

### Connectivity Type

```java
ConnectivityManager cm = (ConnectivityManager) getSystemService(CONNECTIVITY_SERVICE);
NetworkInfo activeNetwork = cm.getActiveNetworkInfo();
```

---

### Check Type

```java
if (activeNetwork.getType() == ConnectivityManager.TYPE_WIFI)
```

---

### IP Address (Wi-Fi)

```java
WifiManager wm = (WifiManager) getApplicationContext().getSystemService(WIFI_SERVICE);
int ip = wm.getConnectionInfo().getIpAddress();
```

---

# 🔄 Data Formatting Layer

## 🎯 Problem:

Raw values are unreadable

## ✅ Solution:

Convert into human-readable format

---

### Example: Bytes → GB

```java
String formatSize(long size) {
    return Formatter.formatFileSize(this, size);
}
```

---

### Example: RAM Display

```text
8192000000 → 8 GB
```

---

# 🔁 Data Loading Strategy

## On Activity Start:

```text
onCreate()
   ↓
Fetch all data once
   ↓
Bind to UI
```

---

## ⚠️ No Real-Time Updates Needed

* This screen is mostly static
* Avoid unnecessary refresh

---

# 🧠 UI Behavior Rules

1. Use **section headers** (Hardware, Software, Network)
2. Keep **text aligned and readable**
3. Avoid clutter (no raw dumps)
4. Show fallback:

```text
"Not Available"
```

---

# 🧩 Reusable UI Component (Recommended)

## Info Row Pattern:

```text
[ Label ]     [ Value ]
RAM           8 GB
Storage       128 GB
```

---

# ⚠️ Edge Cases Handling

| Case                 | Solution             |
| -------------------- | -------------------- |
| Null values          | Show "Not Available" |
| Restricted APIs      | Skip gracefully      |
| Old Android versions | Add version checks   |

---

# 🔥 Minimal Code Flow Summary

```text
onCreate():
   ↓
collectDeviceInfo()
collectHardwareInfo()
collectSoftwareInfo()
collectNetworkInfo()
   ↓
updateUI()
```

---

# 🚀 Output Quality Target

User should:

* Instantly understand device specs
* Not see raw/unformatted data
* Not feel overwhelmed

---

# 📌 Final Note

This activity is:

* Easy to implement
* High perceived value
* Foundation for report generation

